Author-Name: Robert R. Bliss 
Author-Name: Nikolaos Panigirtzoglou 
Title: Option-Implied Risk Aversion Estimates 
Abstract:
 Using a utility function to adjust the risk-neutral PDF embedded in cross
 sections of options, we obtain measures of the risk aversion implied in
 option prices. Using FTSE 100 and S&P 500 options, and both power and
 exponential-utility functions, we estimate the representative agent's
 relative risk aversion (RRA) at different horizons. The estimated
 coefficients of RRA are all reasonable. The RRA estimates are remarkably
 consistent across utility functions and across markets for given horizons.
 The degree of RRA declines broadly with the forecast horizon and is lower
 during periods of high market volatility. Copyright 2004 by The American Finance Association. 
