Author-Name: Stewart Mayhew 
Author-Name: Vassil Mihov 
Title: How Do Exchanges Select Stocks for Option Listing? 
Abstract:
 We investigate the factors influencing the selection of stocks for option
 listing. Exchanges tend to list options on stocks with high trading
 volume, volatility, and market capitalization, but the relative effect of
 these factors has changed over time as markets have evolved. We observe a
 shift from volume toward volatility after the moratorium on new listings
 ended in 1980. Using control sample methodology designed to correct for
 the endogeneity of option listing, we find no evidence that volatility
 declines with option introduction, in contrast to previous studies that do
 not use control samples. Copyright 2004 by The American Finance Association. 
